<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="808" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August 21,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1069.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 941, of the 6th
                            instant, and have to approve your caution in sending a telegram to each
                            American mission in the interior of Turkey requesting information as to
                            the measure of its present and future protection.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>